# Adding Toggle Functionality to Show/Hide Tool Description

You can add a toggle functionality to show/hide the tool descriptions by introducing some state management. Here's how to implement it:

1. First, track which tool descriptions are visible with useState
2. Add a click handler to the toggle button
3. Apply conditional styling based on the visibility state

Here's the implementation:

```jsx
import React from "react";
import {
  motion,
  AnimatePresence,
  useScroll,
  useTransform,
  useSpring,
} from "framer-motion";
import { useState, useRef } from "react";
import { TECH_STACK } from "../constants";
import TechStackItem from "./TechStackItem.jsx";

const SkillList = () => {
  // Create state to track which descriptions are visible
  const [visibleDescriptions, setVisibleDescriptions] = useState({});
  const ref = useRef(null);

  const { scrollYProgress } = useScroll({
    target: ref,
    offset: ["start 80%", "end 70%"],
  });

  const yTransform = useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0, 0.5], [140, 0]);
  const opacityTransform = useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0, 0.5], [0.3, 1]);

  const y = useSpring(yTransform, { stiffness: 100, damping: 20 });
  const opacity = useSpring(opacityTransform, { stiffness: 100, damping: 20 });

  // Toggle description visibility
  const toggleDescription = (stackIndex, toolIndex) => {
    const key = `${stackIndex}-${toolIndex}`;
    setVisibleDescriptions(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      [key]: !prev[key]
    }));
  };

  // Check if a specific description is visible
  const isDescriptionVisible = (stackIndex, toolIndex) => {
    const key = `${stackIndex}-${toolIndex}`;
    return !!visibleDescriptions[key];
  };

  return (
    <div className="container">
      <motion.div
        ref={ref}
        style={{ y, opacity, scrollMarginTop: "100px" }}
        transition={{ ease: "easeOut" }}
        id="adventures"
        className="relative -z-10 mx-auto my-12 w-fit px-12 text-center text-4xl font-bold lg:text-7xl"
      >
        Tech Proficiencies
        <div className="!-bottom-4 mx-auto w-full scale-x-90 rounded-full underline" />
        <div className="!-bottom-4 mx-auto w-full scale-x-90 rounded-full underline blur-sm" />
      </motion.div>

      <div className="before:mask-fade-top-bottom relative flex flex-wrap gap-4 p-4 before:absolute before:inset-0 before:z-[-10] before:rounded-xl before:bg-gradient-to-b before:from-neutral-500/25 before:to-transparent before:backdrop-blur-md max-sm:flex-col">
        {TECH_STACK.map((stack, stackIndex) => (
          <div
            key={stackIndex}
            className="before:grainy-noise flex flex-col gap-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-700/5 pt-4 shadow drop-shadow-sm before:bg-repeat"
          >
            <div className="mx-4 text-lg font-bold text-neutral-400">
              {stack.subtitle}
            </div>
            <div className="mx-4 text-4xl font-bold">{stack.title}</div>
            <div className="mx-4 text-lg">{stack.description}</div>
            <div className="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-4">
              {stack.tools.map((tool, toolIndex) => (
                <div
                  className="bg-neutral-900 p-4 shadow-inner"
                  key={toolIndex}
                >
                  <div className="flex items-center gap-4 rounded-md p-3">
                    {typeof tool.icon === "string" ? (
                      <img
                        src={tool.icon}
                        alt={tool.name}
                        className="m-2 h-12 w-12 rounded-lg bg-white"
                      />
                    ) : (
                      <div className="h-12 w-12">{tool.icon}</div>
                    )}
                    <div className="flex flex-col">
                      <span className="mb-1 text-sm font-medium">
                        {tool.name}
                      </span>
                      <span className="rounded-full bg-white px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-black">
                        {tool.xp}
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <button 
                      className="relative ml-auto mr-4"
                      onClick={() => toggleDescription(stackIndex, toolIndex)}
                      aria-label={isDescriptionVisible(stackIndex, toolIndex) ? "Hide details" : "Show details"}
                    >
                      <div className="absolute -inset-1 left-[6px] h-4 w-0.5 rotate-45 rounded bg-neutral-400" />
                      <div className={`absolute -inset-1 h-4 w-0.5 ${isDescriptionVisible(stackIndex, toolIndex) ? 'rotate-45' : '-rotate-45'} rounded bg-neutral-400`} />
                    </button>
                  </div>
                  <AnimatePresence>
                    {isDescriptionVisible(stackIndex, toolIndex) && (
                      <motion.div 
                        initial={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
                        animate={{ height: "auto", opacity: 1 }}
                        exit={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
                        transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
                        className="overflow-hidden"
                      >
                        <div className="mx-4 text-lg pt-2">{tool.desc}</div>
                      </motion.div>
                    )}
                  </AnimatePresence>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default SkillList;
```

Key improvements:

1. Added a state to track which description is visible using an object with keys based on stack and tool indices
2. Added a toggle function to flip the visibility state
3. Added a helper function to check visibility state
4. Made the description container use AnimatePresence for smooth show/hide animations
5. Changed the second X line to transform based on visibility state (creating a "+" when closed and an "x" when open)
6. Added proper aria-label for accessibility

This implementation will allow users to toggle the visibility of each tool description independently.
